description.narrative:
Diakonias Human Rights and Democracy Programme's overall aim is to support the growth of diverse, vibrant and independent civil society organizations in Cambodia that are enabled to actively engage in and promote human rights, democracy and gender equality. There are three main objectives: 

 1) Democracy: Actors working for democracy have been strengthened in their interaction with authorities and the public; 

 2) Gender equality: A positive trend in guaranteeing gender equality in society, in initiatives, in participation, in decision-making forums and in distribution of
opportunities; 

3) Human rights: Increased respect for human rights enable a secure and safe environment for individual participation in democratic processes in family, work and community.
